1. Download Media creation tool from here:
https://www.microsoft.com/en-ca/software-download/windows10

2. Reboot machine
3. Open, then select 'Creat installation media'
4. Uncheck "Use the recommended options". Ensure it's 64-bit
5. Select ISO file and where to save it.
The ISO file is a virtual and portable replica of a physical disk, used for the OS installation, software distributions, and backups.
